name: Chester's (Ilford)
summary: This week I went East for my wing excursion and it was not worth the bop. It was a case of catfish; the exterior decor lures you in, then the interior decor continues to gas you, then you cop a meal and realize expeditiously it was all a facade. It's a very nice facade though, great to look at and shoot in, but food is the last thing people should be rolling here for.

summary: Krisha joins the rest of the theater group in staging an LGBTQIA+ rally for their theater adviser, Mr. Siwa. Amidst the chaos of preparations, Vince and Leslie uncover Barry and Mando's secret.

name: Como Pode Um Peixe Vivo
summary: Keyla auditions for a musical show. Benê starts giving piano lessons to Nem. Lica gets a freelancer. Tina moves into Lica's house.

name: The Sanctuary
summary: This week, host Wil Wheaton (Star Trek: The Next Generation) is joined by new stars Blu del Barrio (Adira) and Ian Alexander (Gray). The two young actors describe what it's like to join the massive Star Trek family, the impact of playing trans and non-binary characters, and just how hard it is to fake playing the cello.

name: Float My Floral Boat
summary: The final four tackle themed tablescapes before a team challenge that celebrates the LGBTQIA+ community with brilliant floral barges.

name: Room With a Bloom
summary: The final florists create celebratory signature bouquets before transforming empty rooms into vibrant, flower-filled spaces that tell a story stunning enough to snag the life-changing $100,000 grand prize.

name: I Saw Santa Kissing Someone in the Hot Tub
summary: Before Chad, Faith, and Garrett can wine and dine a mystery suitor for their eighth date of Christmas, Garrett receives a sweet surprise. Later, when someone from Faith's past reenters the picture, what's to become of her future with Anthony? Meanwhile, the arrival of a gregarious new housemate puts the others on edge.

name: Ice Ice Baby
summary: With only two dates remaining before our Leads must choose someone to take home, newcomer Chelsea makes up for lost time by commanding control of the festivities—and everyone's attention. After being prematurely friend-zoned by Dominick, Garrett hopes that some one-on-one time will reignite their spark.

name: It's Beginning to Look a Lot Like a Relationship
summary: After ten unforgettable dates filled with wild highs and difficult goodbyes, our leads must decide which of their remaining suitors will go home with them for the holidays. After one final group date and some guidance from loved ones, Chad, Faith, and Garrett face their most emotional elimination ceremony yet.

name: "Virtue Signal"
summary: Virtue Signal takes a look at the Trump pardon scandals, Bill Barr's denial of widespread voter fraud, and more with actor Aasif Mandvi. Plus, Kylie Weaver empowers America's female warmongers.

name: Quid Pro Quo
summary: Andrew cuts ties with Sarah while Dikhan learns about Andrew's lie. Lynn's new addiction is a surprise to Brian. Lacey goes on assignment while Marva has her eyes on Oliver.

name: All is Lost
summary: J.W. and Marco's injuries are an opportunity for the rest of the team to step up, including sophomore Jett, but external pressures cause some of the team to lose focus.

name: Murphy's Law
summary: Sam and AJ settle into their new life and apartment but quickly realize that there's more to Freeman Lakes than meets the eye.

name: The Woman Who Dressed America
summary: Four potential associates tackle a fashion challenge for the chance to help Jenna Lyons redesign her first client's classic Brooklyn brownstone.

name: How High Low Can You Go?
summary: Jenna challenges two associates to help her transform a raw loft space into her company's new headquarters using a high/low fashion technique.

name: Dinner Party Drama
summary: A third group of associates sets out to create a fabulous table setting before two are chosen to help Jenna execute a fabulous party and photoshoot in LA.

name: Meet Your Makers
summary: After narrowing down the pool of associates, Jenna asks the group to find unique, locally crafted products for her new pop-up shop.

name: Fashion Bus
summary: Four associates join Jenna and team on a road trip to give style makeovers to two women with fashion dilemmas.  Back in NYC, Jenna must decide who's going home.

name: Open House and Broken Hearts
summary: The remaining associates help Jenna redesign her upstate house, but will they be able to work as a team to bring cozy-chic vibes to the space?

name: Reinventing Date Night
summary: Emotions run high as the remaining associates divide into teams to help Jenna give three couples high-fashion date night transformations.

name: Dream Job
summary: The final associates design their own socially-distant pop-up experiences as they await Jenna's official hiring decision.

name: The Single Guy
summary: Erick's father makes a surprise weekend visit with the hopes of getting to know Lisa better. Patricia urges Jason and Alexandria to settle down. Jason reluctantly rolls solo to his married friends' get-together and the event quickly goes downhill.
